==Continuity==
The novelization has a number of differences from the film:
*The novel adds several scenes with the probe droid and its journey to locate the Rebel base on Hoth. In one, the droid is attacked by a [[Wampa/Legends|wampa]]. The probe droid reacts by disintegrating the creature with its blaster. In another, the droid creates a [[Force field/Legends|force field]] to shield itself from a snowstorm.
*Han Solo never says, "And I thought they smelled bad on the outside." Instead he mentions that if he doesn't get the shelter built in time, "[[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] won't need those [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]]."
*[[Maximilian Veers/Legends|General Veers]] is killed when a Rebel [[snowspeeder]] crashes into his [[All Terrain Armored Transport|Imperial walker]], blowing it up. This is based on a [[Content cut from Star Wars|deleted scene]] from the film.
*[[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] has blue skin instead of his recognizable green. This is based on earlier designs for the character, the same as the blue-skinned Yoda appearing in ''[[The Marvel Comics Illustrated Version of Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back|The Marvel Comics Illustrated Version of The Empire Strikes Back]]''. 
*Luke undergoes additional training sessions with Yoda not depicted in the film. In one, he tries and fails to leap across a pond. In another, he trains with two, then four [[Remote/Legends|remotes]] that fire stinging blasts similar to that in ''[[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|A New Hope]].'' 
*C-3PO does not interrupt Han and Leia's first kiss, but [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] witnesses part of the scene.
*There are only five bounty hunters aboard the ''Executor''. [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]] is omitted, and [[Zuckuss/Legends|Zuckuss]] is a "human type" instead of a [[Gand]].
*Vader's lightsaber in Luke's vision in the [[Cave of Evil/Legends|Dark Side Cave]] is blue rather than red.
*When greeting the ''Millennium Falcon'' on the landing platform, [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian's]] entourage includes aliens and droids.
*[[Lobot/Legends|Lobot]] is described in vague terms. He is referred to only as "Lando's aide" and "wore a radio device that wrapped around his head and covered both his ears." He is not identified as a [[Cyborg/Legends|cyborg]]. He also talks, in contrast to his mute portrayal in the film but consistent with portrayals in other media.
*The [[Ugnaught/Legends|Ugnaughts]] are throwing scrap into a pool of molten metal instead of putting them onto a conveyor belt that carries them into an incinerator. Chewbacca also has far less trouble in forcing them to relinquish Threepio's parts.
*When Leia tells Han that she loves him, Han replies, "Just remember that, because I'll be back"&mdash;instead of his famous line from the film, "I know."
*As the ''Millennium Falcon'' flies toward Luke as he dangles from a [[Weather vane|vane]] on Cloud City's underside, the structure breaks, and Luke begins to plummet. Chewbacca, flying the ''Falcon'', has to execute a fast dive in order to catch him.

